## Overview
Status of Relationships Analysis is a framework used by government officials to analyze and visualize the status of their relationships with various stakeholders present in a meeting or consultation process.

## Purpose
The purpose of this tool is to help government officials make informed decisions on how to build, maintain, or improve relationships with different actors based on their predisposition to collaborate and dialogue attitude.

## How it works
This framework involves ranking interactions between the main agency hosting the consultation and other stakeholders in two dimensions: predisposition to collaborate and dialogue attitude. The information is then systematized and visualized in a map, showing the status of relationships from "excellent" to "in crisis".

## Requirements
To effectively use this tool, individuals must be focused and attentive to subtle hints present in dialogue, such as tone, volume, and content.
